Comex silver futures opened 15 to 18cents higher and then retreated slightly as followthroughbuying slowed.    May was up 12.5 cents at 6.705 dlrs from a high of 6.75dlrs. July was up 13.1 cents at 6.785 dlrs from 6.84 dlrs.    Traders said large commission houses were buyers on theopen but encountered profit-taking and a slowdown in orders.    Some traders said the market is starting to look overboughttechnically and vulnerable to a correction.    But they added that speculators continue to view the marketas a good buy relative to gold. Reuter&#3;